                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.008 North Pacific/282b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-02-07T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 7, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Because of situation outlined in Department’s 39, February 4, 6 p.m., it
                    would greatly contribute to desired purpose and we would be relieved of possible
                    embarrassment if an early reply to your representations could be obtained from
                    the Japanese Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
